TODO
====

Done
----
[x] $0 writes are now silently discarded instead of erroring.
[x] SRA/SRAV do an arithmetic shift and no longer clobber the source.
[x] Branch offsets are sign-extended and relative to the delay slot.
[x] Loads/stores sign-extend their immediate offset.
[x] Delay-slot handling reworked into a clean branch-delay pipeline; all
    branches (incl. bgez/bltz/bgezal/bltzal via REGIMM rt decoding) run
    their delay slot exactly once.
[x] mult/multu/div/divu write HI/LO in the correct order.
[x] addi/addiu/slti/sltiu sign-extend their immediate.
[x] Implemented lb, lbu, lh, lhu, lwl, lwr, sb, sh, swl, swr; fixed the
    byte-addressed memory helpers.
[x] break instruction.
[x] Compiler warnings (logger.c, map_elf.c) cleaned up.

Tests
-----
[x] Added per-instruction tests covering logic, shifts, arithmetic,
    HI/LO moves, set-less-than, branches, jump-and-link, byte/half and
    unaligned load-stores, char syscalls, exit2, break, overflow ($k0)
    and file I/O. The suite passes 31/31; cpu.c 96%, functions.c 95%,
    syscalls.c 94%.
[ ] Cover the divide-by-zero paths and the read_string error path.

Done (was bonus / latent bugs)
------------------------------
[x] ELF loading: PT_LOAD segments are copied into emulated memory and
    execution starts at e_entry (src/map_elf.c).
[x] Fixed SLTU function code (was 0x29, must be 0x2b) - sltu never worked.
[x] exit2 now always halts; unknown syscalls halt with an error.
[x] Overflow in add/addi/sub now writes 1 to $k0 (0 otherwise) per the
    subject, instead of aborting via clean_exit() (which was a
    use-after-free). $k0 is readable, so this is now testable.
[x] File syscalls: _open maps the subject's read/write flag to real
    open(2) flags (O_CREAT|O_TRUNC for write); open/read/write/close
    verified by a round-trip test.

Architecture
------------
[x] decode.h: instruction field accessors (op/rs/rt/rd/shamt/imm16/
    target26/funct) + grouped ISA constants. Removes the field bit-
    twiddling that was duplicated across every decoder.
[x] disasm.c: a single pure disassembler shared by the -l trace and (next)
    the debugger. Replaces the ~300 lines of parallel decode in logger.c
    that kept drifting from the executor (it now knows the MIPS32 ops too).
[x] cpu.c: uses the accessors, advances pc and logs centrally, and follows
    one convention (simple ops inline, multi-line ops in functions.c).
    Shrank from ~400 to ~230 lines.

Bonus roadmap (easiest -> hardest)
----------------------------------
[x] 1. MIPS32: mul, madd/maddu, msub/msubu, clz/clo, movz/movn.
[x] 2. Integrated debugger (src/dbg.c, -d flag): rewritten to share the
       single-step pipeline (step_instruction in cpu.c) and the shared
       disassembler. Commands: step [n], continue, break/delete/
       breakpoints, registers, print, memory [n], code, help, exit.
       Works with piped scripts (not just a TTY), so it is covered by the
       suite via a new optional "flags" field in test_suite.py.
[x] 3. FPU / COP1 (src/fpu.c): f0-f31 register file + condition flag, a
       COP1 decode path (opcode 0x11) and the FP load/store opcodes.
       Implements mtc1/mfc1, lwc1/swc1/ldc1/sdc1, single- and double-
       precision add/sub/mul/div/sqrt/abs/neg/mov, conversions
       (cvt.{s,d,w}.*), compares (c.{eq,lt,le}.*) and bc1t/bc1f. Test
       programs assemble with -mhard-float.
[x] 4. Game system (src/device.c): a memory-mapped GPU. The program draws
       ARGB pixels into a framebuffer (GPU_FB), presents a frame by storing
       to GPU_FLUSH, and reads keys from GPU_INPUT. Rendered with SDL2
       (detected via pkg-config; falls back to a no-op when SDL is absent,
       and SDL is initialised lazily so non-graphical programs open no
       window). Demo: test/game.s (a movable block, w/a/s/d to move).

Extra
-----
[x] JIT compilation (src/jit.c, -j flag): a basic-block JIT to x86-64.
    Runs of simple ALU instructions are compiled to native code in an
    executable buffer and cached per guest PC; branches, memory, mult/div,
    traps, syscalls and FP fall back to the interpreter (which keeps delay
    slots correct). Verified byte-identical to the interpreter across the
    suite; ~3x faster on an arithmetic-heavy loop.

(GDB remote stub dropped in favour of improving the existing debugger.)
